Detailed Description

Class Definition CTagReportContentSelector for LLRP parameter TagReportContentSelector.

  • Document Reference LLRP Specification Section 13.2.1.1

  • Document Reference LLRP Specification Section 16.2.7.1.1

This parameter is used to configure the contents that are of interest in TagReportData. If enabled, the field is reported along with the tag data in the TagReportData.

void LLRP::CTagReportContentSelector::assimilateSubParameters (  CErrorDetails *  pError  )  [virtual]
 

Assimilates the decoded sub-parameters into m_listAllSubParameters.

After fields are decoded, the CDecoder itself takes care of gathering the subparameters into m_listAllSubParameters. Once the end of the enclosing TLV (or message) is reached this assimilateSubParameters() function is called to create parameter refrences from the primary member variables.
